article.description: Kion Brown hit a hook shot in the lane as time ran out, lifting Radford to a 69-67 victory over North Carolina-Wilmington on Saturday.
article.headline: Radford beats NC-Wilmington 69-67 on buzzer beater
article.linkText: Radford beats NC-Wilmington 69-67 on buzzer beater
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Kion Brown hit a hook shot in the lane as time ran out, lifting Radford to a 69-67 victory over North Carolina-Wilmington on Saturday. Brown scored four of his career-high 17 points in the final 39 seconds as Radford (7-5) battled to get past the Seahawks (5-3). Radford won on a buzzer-beater for the third time this season. With North Carolina-Wilmington (5-3) down five in the last three minutes, Chris Flemmings started a 7-0 rally and tied the game at 65 with 1:03 left. Brown and Craig Ponder traded baskets to push the tie to 67 and Radford called a timeout with 11 seconds left. Brown's hook shot rolled in as the buzzer sounded. Taj Owens scored a career-high 16 points with three assists and three steals. Flemmings scored 16 points on 6-for-8 shooting, C.J. Bryce added 14, while Ponder and Jordon Talley had 10 each. The lead changed hands eight times with seven ties.
